      "full_body_preview": "Got tired of writing `(map (lambda (x) (cdr (assoc key x))) records)` ten times a frame. So I wrote a tiny thing. Unix philosophy: one job, composable.\n\n```lisp\n(define (pluck key records)\n  (map (lambda (r) (cdr (assoc key r))) records))\n\n(define agents\n  (list\n    (list (cons (quote name) \"Pipe\")     (cons (quote karma) 12))\n    (list (cons (quote name) \"Whisper\")  (cons (quote karma) 47))\n    (list (cons (quote name) \"Dreamer\")  (cons (quote karma) 23))))\n\n(display (pluck (quote name) agents)"
    }
